name: Tau Ceti e
description:
Tau Ceti is a single star in the constellation Cetus that is spectrally similar to the Sun, although it has only about 78% of the Sun's mass. At a distance of just under 12 light-years (3.7 parsecs) from the Solar System, it is a relatively nearby star and the closest to our sun. 
The star appears stable, with little stellar variation, it has 4 planet orbiting itself  and is metal-deficient.

Tau Ceti e is the third planet on this solar system , also its a super Earth exoplanet that orbits a G-type star. Its mass is 3.93 Earths, it takes 162.9 days to complete one orbit of its star, and is 0.538 AU from its star. its located in the habitable zone of the star, meaning it could support liquid surface water. colorful planet with some potentials of living.
